
[1]pursuit

   PURSUIT, n. The act of following with a view to overtake; a following
   with haste, either for sport or in hostility; as the pursuit of game;
   the pursuit of an enemy.

   1. A following with a view to reach, accomplish or obtain; endeavor to
   attain to or gain; as the pursuit of knowledge; the pursuit of
   happiness or pleasure; the pursuit of power, of honor, of distinction,
   of a phantom.

   2. Proceeding; course of business or occupation; continued employment
   with a view to some end; as mercantile pursuits; literary pursuits.

   3. Prosecution; continuance of endeavor.
